Overview

In the past couple of years, there has been a significant evolution within the E-commerce sector, impacting both businesses and consumers alike. This transformation is characterized by a growing customer base, the expansion of omnichannel retailing, shifts in consumer preferences, a heightened expectation for seamless cross-channel communication, and the emergence of faster delivery services. As a result, there is now a paramount emphasis on developing a resilient and efficient supply chain capable of delivering a premium, swift, and uninterrupted customer experience. Modern E-commerce retailers are actively pursuing sophisticated supply chain networks that seamlessly integrate various elements such as material sourcing, warehousing, inventory management spanning both-offline and online sales channels, efficient delivery services, and streamlined communication with customers.

The rapidly evolving needs of both consumers and retailers have expanded the scope of supply chains, driving the adoption of digital consumer behaviors and the integration of AI and ML in supply chain management. It is now crucial for retailers, future supply chain leaders, and organizations to develop action plans that identify key focus areas, outline mitigation strategies, and embrace technological advancements.

The E COMCONNECT: E-Commerce Logistics Conference will convene experienced supply chain leaders from retail, e-commerce, and D2C sectors to showcase various strategies for achieving more with fewer resources, enhancing cost efficiency, and adapting to the increasing emphasis on sustainability.
